<!--
This is the menu displayed at the top of the page for logged in members.

They can navigate to the following pages:

Play Gym - Redirects member to sign up page
Dashboard - Redirects member to member dashboard
About - Redirects member to 'about' page which includes a brief description of the application.
User Icon - Redirects member to 'edit details' page where user details are displayed and they can update existing profile
information
Logout - Logs member out. Login page rendered following logout.

jQuery script is used to mark the active item in the menu (dependent on what page the member is on).
-->

<nav class="ui menu">
    <header class="ui header item"><a href="/signup"> Play Gym</a></header>
    <div class="right menu">
        <a id="dashboard" class="item" href="/dashboard"> Dashboard </a>
        <a id="about" class="item" href="/about"> About </a>
        <a id="user" class="item" href="/viewAccountDetails"> <i class="user icon"></i></a>
        <a id="logout" class="item" href="/logout"> Logout </a>
    </div>
</nav>

<script>
    $("#${_id}").addClass("active item");
</script>